Did You Know?
Pannage Is the Practice of Letting Domestic Pigs Loose onto The Forest Land for
A Minimum Off 60 Days to Hoover Up All the Fallen Nuts Which Are Poisonous
to The Ponies! This Is Common Practice Between Late September and Mid
November!

Who Are?
Commoners Of the Forest Are Those Who Occupy Land or
Property Where Privileges Are Attached. This Does Include
the Right to Graze Stock on The Open Forest!
Verderers Are Forestry Officials in England Who Deal with
Common Land in Certain Formal Royal Hunting Areas Which
Are Property of The Crown!
.
Commissioners Are Government Officials Responsible for
Protecting, Expanding & Promoting Sustainable
Management of Forest Land!

The New Forest Is Steeped with History, Heritage and Tales of Folklore from Family to Family and Village to
Village. Some Stories May Be Scary, Unbelievable and Some Too Curious to Be Reality. Overtime, These Stories
Have Taken Shape Through the Art of Storytelling, Woven from Locals, Authors and The Vast Trade
Throughout the Forest.
